                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. Your 24, November 10, 6 p.m., penultimate paragraph. There is no present
                    prospect of a repeal or a suspension or a modification of the existing
                    neutrality legislation and you should proceed on the assumption that no such
                    action will occur.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
